          <h2>
            Ben /
                         Anthony
            
          </h2>
        </header>
        <div class="content">
          <div class="summary">
            <p>The future of the application development isn't going to be a
single-vendor, compiled experience. It'll be open and free for all.
Starting today, we're going to live it.</p>

          </div>
          
 
          <figure class="intro">
  <!-- <img src="../../content/drafts/2.currencies/w3c-article-header.png" alt=""> -->
</figure>

<dl class="ben">
  <dt>Ben/</dt>
  <dd>
    <h3>The project</h3>
    <p class="note">Perhaps a left column link to the install site and a screen shot here?</p>
    <p>Like anyone else, I could have logged into the app store, read some reviews, then skeptically tapped on the "buy now" button.</p>
    
    <p><strike>I'd known about localStorage for quite some time, even using it for a billable project (only once!), but it felt like no one had ever really going past googling 'iphone css app'.</strike></p>

    <h3>The descent</h3>
    <p>With everyone seemingly jostleing to own the dominant mobile web framework, you'd think that we'd have some solid options through competition.</p>
    
    <aside>
      <div id='embedly_twitter_40264114' class='embedly_twitter'<p>Was asked why I "insist on coding JS from scratch" for mobile. jQTouch: 100k. jQ mobile: 160k. Sencha: 400k. My script: 1k. That's why.<span class='embedly_timestamp'><a title='Thu Jan 20 02:20:20 +0000 2011' href='http://twitter.com/pixi_stix/status/27913287215620096'>Jan 20</a> via web</span><span class='metadata'><span class='author'><a href='http://twitter.com/pixi_stix'><img src='http://a1.twimg.com/profile_images/373263968/DSC08216_normal.jpg' /></a><strong><a href='http://twitter.com/pixi_stix'>Colleen O'Banion</a></strong><br/>pixi_stix</span></span></p></div>
    </aside>

    <p>Projects like PhoneGap and jQtouch have "commoditised" the act of building a mobile application for iOS devices, yet I'm still yet to see an app that I wanted to actually use that used either of these frameworks.</p>
    <p class="note">Maybe Anthony can lay in on this bit following?</p>
    <p>Of course, this isn't a problem with the technology, its a design/mindset problem.</p>
    
  </dd>
</dl>

<dl class="anthony">
  <dt>Anthony/</dt>
  <dd>
    <h3>Starting out</h3>

    <p>We both agreed that there was some interesting potential here. The idea of designing an iphone app in html was definitely an appealing one, coming from where we come from. So I took the initial proof-of-concept and started designing it as a real app.</p>

